Britain anticipates an imminent statement from the IRA regarding a potential shift away from violence, sparking hope for a new era in Northern Irish politics.
Expectations are high for the IRA to announce a disarmament plan by the end of June.
Despite progress since the 1998 Good Friday peace deal, concerns remain over ongoing criminal activities.
Political figures stress the importance of IRA cooperation for lasting peace.
Efforts to revive power-sharing have faced obstacles, with demands for concrete actions from the IRA.
The IRA's response will be crucial in determining the future of Northern Ireland's peace process.
